# Entity status

## Direction

**All listable entities will have a `status` field** (user and admin portals). Each entity gets its **own status union** and label keys when its workflow differs. Reuse **`StatusBadgeComponent`** for pill UI and **`--status-*` theme tokens** in `src/styles.scss`; do not invent per-feature badge markup.

**Today:** user routes, cargo, and storage temporarily share `UserEntityStatus` from `shared/constants/user-entity-status.ts`. When an entity needs different statuses, define e.g. `VehicleStatus` in that feature and entity-specific i18n under `portal.<portal>.features.<entity>.status.*` — then widen `StatusBadgeComponent` (e.g. optional `labelKey` input) if labels are no longer in `shared.entityStatus.*`.

## Shared pieces

| Piece | Path |
|-------|------|
| Status type (interim) | `shared/constants/user-entity-status.ts` — `UserEntityStatus`, `USER_ENTITY_STATUS_LABEL_KEYS` |
| Badge widget | `shared/ui/status-badge/` — `app-status-badge`, `status` input |
| Theme tokens | `src/styles.scss` — `--status-open-bg`, `--status-open-text`, `--status-in-progress-*`, `--status-canceled-*`, `--status-closed-*` (light + dark) |
| Badge labels (interim) | `shared.entityStatus.*` in `en.json` / `bh.json` |
| Column header | `portal.<portal>.features.<entity>.table.columns.status` |

`UserEntityStatus`: `'open' | 'in_progress' | 'canceled' | 'closed'`.

## Status colors

Workflow hues in `styles.scss` (`--status-*-bg`, `--status-*-text`). Consumed **only** by `StatusBadgeComponent` — not entity service colors (`--entity-*`) or metric-card variants.

| Status | Hue | Light text | Dark text | Meaning |
|--------|-----|------------|-----------|---------|
| `open` | Green (`#22c55e`) | `#16a34a` | `#4ade80` | Available / accepting interest |
| `in_progress` | Blue (`#3b82f6`) | `#2563eb` | `#60a5fa` | Active deal in motion |
| `canceled` | Red (`#ef4444`) | `#dc2626` | `#f87171` | Terminated |
| `closed` | Amber (`#f59e0b`) | `#d97706` | `#fbbf24` | Finished / no longer active |

**`open` is green** (not amber) so status pills stay distinct from freight entity chrome (`#ea580c`). Change hues only in `styles.scss` — do not hardcode status hex in components.

## Entity `data/` conventions

- Add `status: …` on the **entity** interface (`Route`, `Cargo`, …) — **not** on form models unless status becomes user-editable.
- Mock data: seed varied statuses for demo.
- Service `create()`: set default status (e.g. `'open'`) **before** spreading payload so forms cannot override.
- Service `update()`: spread existing row first so `status` is preserved when not in the form payload.

## Table display

Second column after the primary identifier; `cell: 'custom'`, `sortable: true`, `width: ~9rem`.

**Visual rule:** `StatusBadgeComponent` is the **only colored pill** in a table row. Route chips use neutral `--chip-neutral-*` tokens; dates use plain `DateRangeDisplayComponent` text — see `tables.mdc`.

**Filter chips / multi-select / option tiles / collapsed flyout summary:** status filters use `showStatusBadges: true` — `StatusBadgeComponent` only (no duplicate label text). Vehicle type filters use `showOptionIcons: true` — `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent` only (no inline Lucide icons). See `table-filters.mdc`.

```typescript
{ key: 'status', titleKey: '…table.columns.status', sortable: true, cell: 'custom', width: '9rem' }
export const statusCellKey = tableCellKey(EntityTable, 'status');
```

```html
<ng-template [appTableCell]="statusKey" let-row>
  <app-status-badge [status]="row.status" />
</ng-template>
```

Reference: `portal/user/features/transport/table/`, `cargo/table/`, `storage/table/`.

## Detail page display

User portal detail pages show status in **`EntityDetailSummaryComponent`** (right side of summary band, **same row on mobile**) — not in `DetailView` / `*.detail.ts`. Same rule: status badge is the **only colored pill** on the page. See `detail-page.mdc`.

**Not** entity service-type colors (`--entity-*` / `entityTab`) — those are navigation/context chrome only; see `entity-service-colors.mdc`.

## Checklist for a new entity

1. `{Entity}Status` union + label-key map in `*.model.ts` or `*.constants.ts`
2. `status` on entity + mock data + service defaults
3. `status` table column + `StatusBadgeComponent` in table page
4. i18n: `table.columns.status` + status label keys (`shared.entityStatus.*` only while sharing the interim union)

Related: `tables.mdc`, `layout.mdc`, `shared-constants.mdc`, `i18n.mdc`, `portal-feature.mdc`, `entity-service-colors.mdc`
